    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5821" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λί̄ην</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">too,
            excessively, greatly, very;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μή τι λίην προκαλίζεο</span>, provoke me not
          ‘too far,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 18.20</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; οὐδέ τι λί̄ην οὕτω νώνυμός ἐστι</span>, not
          so <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">very</span> unrenowned, <i><span class="en">Od.
            13.238</span></i>, cf. <i><span class="en">Od. 15.405</span></i>;
          often <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καὶ λίην</span> at the beginning of a
          statement, ‘most certainly,’ ‘ay, by all means,’ etc.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
